@node part1 "What is it?"



            EasyConvert is a program which offers conversions between various
            measurements.

            It is called 'EasyConvert' because I would like to think that it
            is easy to use.

            The interface is now fully font sensitive - it will use your
            own screen font (as used in your Workbench screen titles).

            You also have access to the system clipboard.
            (With the exception of OS3.5's Editpad which doesn't seem
             to store its clipboard data where I can look for it).

            It is also possible to hide the program in the Tools menu.


            To discover why I created EasyConvert click @{"here" link part5}.

            If you want to run it you'll want to know the @{"system requirements" link part2}.

            Or jump straight to @{"usage" link part4} for instructions on
            how to access the program.


                        @{"Return to contents" link main}
@endnode

@node part2 "System Requirements"

            @{b}@{u}Minimum system required (this is untested):@{uu}@{ub}

            An Amiga, 60Kb RAM, Workbench 2.05

            @{b}@{u}Recommended system:@{uu}@{ub}

            Amiga1200, 100Kb RAM free, Workbench 3.9


            @{b}@{u}Development system:@{uu}@{ub}

            @{b}Hardware@{ub}
            Amiga PPC in Power Tower, Blizzard PPC 603e+/210 & 060/50 with 80Mb RAM,
            6.4Gb hard disk, Philips 109S10 19" monitor,
            2Gb JAZ2 drive, Pace 'Solo' 56K Modem.

            @{b}Software@{ub}
            Workbench 3.9, StormC4.0 (GCC)

                        @{"Return to contents" link main}
@endnode

